Date: Tue, 19 May 2015 20:32:55 +0300
Subject: [PATCH 0531/1077] drm/i915: Use ilk_init_lp_watermarks() on BDW
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

commit 7ad0dbab20678709ca268afa54189cf49b058f15 upstream.

We're not using ilk_init_lp_watermarks() on BDW for some reason.
Probably due to the BDW patches and the relevant WM patches landing
roughlly at the same time. Fix it up.

Signed-off-by: Ville Syrjälä <ville.syrjala@linux.intel.com>
Reviewed-by: Jesse Barnes <jbarnes@virtuousgeek.org>
Signed-off-by: Daniel Vetter <daniel.vetter@ffwll.ch>
Signed-off-by: Pengyu Ma <pengyu.ma@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/i915/intel_pm.c | 4 +---
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/intel_pm.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/intel_pm.c
index 5792132..cb01ee9 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/intel_pm.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/intel_pm.c
@@ -6173,9 +6173,7 @@ static void broadwell_init_clock_gating(struct drm_device *dev)
 	struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
 	enum pipe pipe;
 
-	I915_WRITE(WM3_LP_ILK, 0);
-	I915_WRITE(WM2_LP_ILK, 0);
-	I915_WRITE(WM1_LP_ILK, 0);
+	ilk_init_lp_watermarks(dev);
 
 	/* WaSwitchSolVfFArbitrationPriority:bdw */
 	I915_WRITE(GAM_ECOCHK, I915_READ(GAM_ECOCHK) | HSW_ECOCHK_ARB_PRIO_SOL);
